<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="35" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 832.61333/76.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Attorney General</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of Justice</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Will you kindly give formal authority to
                            your Mr. Joseph J. Slechta, Vice and Deputy Consul General of the United
                            States at Rio de Janeiro, to give to this Department, and particularly
                            to Mr. William T. Chantland, Special Assistant to the Attorney General,
                            who has the matter in charge, all the facts and information he has
                            relative to the Brazilian coffee valorization scheme.</p>
                        <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. A. Fowler</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>